<body>
    <h1>20260507 - Lapu-Lapu GOCC and Japan</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <h1 local-id=3D"a7b3c1b16d7e" id=3D"id-20260507-Lapu-LapuGOCCandJap=
an-ApplicationMonitoringOnboarding&amp;DashboardReview=E2=80=93MeetingNotes=
">Application Monitoring Onboarding &amp; Dashboard Review =E2=80=93 Meetin=
g Notes</h1>
<p local-id=3D"ab4e4fb8021d"></p>
<p local-id=3D"b3d40f75806c"><strong><u>Implementation Plan</u></strong></p=
>
<p local-id=3D"6e5bfd8916b7"><a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://one=
.newrelic.com/dashboards/detail/MTczNzcwNXxWSVp8REFTSEJPQVJEfGRhOjEyMDUxOTg=
y?account=3D1737705&amp;state=3D95432be6-14bc-fb31-5335-6225a8c7d447" rel=
=3D"nofollow">GOCC &lt; New Relic</a> - GOCC Japan Application Dashboard wi=
th synthetic, APM and metrics</p>
<p local-id=3D"d0fb5458ee43">Prod - <strong>Employee Experience Dashboard <=
/strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"6455ceb2c69d">
<li local-id=3D"a731cde5115a">
<p local-id=3D"2a7af7596e06">Decision to escalate non-standard monitoring a=
pps rather than workaround - If PS Team already has ID set up thru New Reli=
c then use as-is, otherwise escalate for Dev-team resolution. [<em>opportun=
ity</em>] Old dashboards may contain URLs that have already been set up.</p=
></li>
<li local-id=3D"4a02a1a90860">
<p local-id=3D"61517e5129f2">68/88 Japan Application Systems complete (77%)=
</p>
<ul local-id=3D"dc95b90c978e">
<li local-id=3D"803cf5dc24b2">
<p local-id=3D"215b183eeda1">Confirm alerting/incident workflows</p></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"fdd5dbc8bef3">Non-Prod -<strong> Developer Experience Dashbo=
ard</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"20a8e8746464">
<li local-id=3D"c499b4cdbc57">
<p local-id=3D"8dfa48c3718b">50/60 Groups of App Environments (83%)</p>
<ul local-id=3D"9ff368b82029">
<li local-id=3D"251c1bb3-34fc-48dd-89f8-a309d1faac1e">
<p local-id=3D"5fdb7443475f">Confirm alerting/incident workflows</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"76a83110-d472-4a78-a0ff-a6b2095ffa73">
<p local-id=3D"10ff46d4ed73">APM/metrics based monitoring</p></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"8043234373e5"><strong>Transition App Monitoring and BAU Oper=
ations to GOCC</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"e8767fd65eca">
<li local-id=3D"6596ac3b9314">
<p local-id=3D"6b36084452c7">25/65 - Go-Live L0/L1 in GOCC</p></li>
</ul>
<h1 local-id=3D"79a3808603d3" id=3D"id-20260507-Lapu-LapuGOCCandJapan-Walkt=
hruAlert/IncidentManagement(Jonan,George)"><strong>Walkthru Alert/Incident =
Management </strong>(Jonan, George)</h1>
<h1 local-id=3D"28a63d71a200" id=3D"id-20260507-Lapu-LapuGOCCandJapan-Decis=
ions">Decisions</h1>
<ul local-id=3D"77f4eca1-3d81-4fcf-b2eb-5870c64b8da5">
<li local-id=3D"35304ffa-9e52-4874-b9af-bfcecd147abd">
<p local-id=3D"bd9566b2c045">Onboarded applications included in GOCC alert =
handling, priority by application tier.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"8c7e3bdb-73e7-43e3-89bc-2a090a83c24b">
<p local-id=3D"0c256e6c03eb">Rapid recovery plans must be integrated into S=
erviceNow for incident management.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"0a0ea437-5321-4d62-9397-1922a73cbcb6">
<p local-id=3D"0e5aad9c2ea4">Recurring incidents mapped to existing problem=
 tickets for tracking and management.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"5481a112-b308-4f35-9303-eac743db5bcc">
<p local-id=3D"6ef338c1b65a">XMatters group rosters for Japan reviewed and =
escalation flows configured.</p></li>
</ul>
<h1 local-id=3D"2ba5e160f76d" id=3D"id-20260507-Lapu-LapuGOCCandJapan-Openq=
uestions">Open questions</h1>
<ul local-id=3D"9fde06cc-f777-4e0c-8ced-145cb9736c4c">
<li local-id=3D"f73ad223-bb32-4faa-98cb-198c81dcf412">
<p local-id=3D"feec11353663">Detection time for non-onboarded applications =
may be longer or missed entirely.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"eaebf8b3-4831-471f-b814-33deea772eba">
<p local-id=3D"740d038b62a4">Integration process for rapid recovery plans i=
nto ServiceNow is not finalized.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"8aee741a-179f-4771-881a-b507cfbb3ed8">
<p local-id=3D"5c0579819e14">Automating correlation of incidents to problem=
 records is still under consideration.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"69867926-bef8-43d4-b978-a35bca4cf5f6">
<p local-id=3D"5c4c4fbe76d8">Optimal structure for L1, L2, L3 escalation gr=
oups is undetermined.</p></li>
</ul>
<h1 local-id=3D"df1100905de5" id=3D"id-20260507-Lapu-LapuGOCCandJapan-Agend=
a">Agenda</h1>
<p local-id=3D"ae4cc5ff4919">Operational Resilience objective review - Scop=
e</p>
<p local-id=3D"45e5954e53fd">Shared collaboration space (Jira, SP, Confluen=
ce, Planner)</p>
<p local-id=3D"4390727b7ce0">Agree on source(s) of truth</p>
<p local-id=3D"cd1725535e87">Establish baseline metrics for monitoring</p>
<h1 local-id=3D"e5c045a8dc32" id=3D"id-20260507-Lapu-LapuGOCCandJapan-Meeti=
ngnotes">Meeting notes</h1>
<h3 local-id=3D"356582aef48f" id=3D"id-20260507-Lapu-LapuGOCCandJapan-Alert=
processoverview">Alert process overview</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"17c2fadd-7033-4c0f-9b60-33d01ae50949">
<li local-id=3D"76cd6245-8300-46b2-bb8c-9c6c99bfcfc2">
<p local-id=3D"b80c0aef3bae">George explained that the alert response workf=
low for onboarded applications involves the team assessing and validating a=
lerts according to the runbook.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"c5d8b4be-3e8d-4982-9320-6884c522d38a">
<p local-id=3D"f557d068ef39">Jonan clarified that applications not yet onbo=
arded do not have alert policies routed to GOCC, making them technically ou=
t of scope for GOCC's alert response.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"58049886-d507-4494-9010-2fa68f38d8ad">
<p local-id=3D"a3e1e6f5f9f2">Jonan stated that unmonitored events from non-=
onboarded applications may be reported through service desk, customer incid=
ents, or application teams, resulting in longer detection times or no GOCC =
involvement.</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"aaab8d7cc819" id=3D"id-20260507-Lapu-LapuGOCCandJapan-Alert=
processscope">Alert process scope</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"37836c97-288c-414d-baa0-71f2237e0f64">
<li local-id=3D"47080745-1a31-4022-a90e-90db409778ed">
<p local-id=3D"4d6d6aa7b73f">Jonan explained that applications not onboarde=
d to GOCC may generate alerts, but these are not routed to GOCC and are ins=
tead reported through service desk, customer incidents, or application team=
s, leading to longer detection times or no GOCC involvement.</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"402b441b2eee" id=3D"id-20260507-Lapu-LapuGOCCandJapan-Incid=
entprioritization">Incident prioritization</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"36e4c4e7-a398-48d3-baf2-0f7cfedd2015">
<li local-id=3D"e8d85b99-7907-40c1-8483-a7d65a89e16c">
<p local-id=3D"ac970759b876">George described that incident priority differ=
s by application tier: gold applications are assigned P1 or P2, silver are =
P2 or P3, and bronze are P3 during business hours.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"89a55a17-7d32-41e9-9ac8-467ec7146c1a">
<p local-id=3D"5c398d07fd3b">Jonan and George described that managed P3 inc=
idents are raised to prevent major incidents and typically require a techni=
cal bridge, while normal P3 incidents have minimal impact and do not requir=
e a bridge.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"aeb10ef0-7597-4ee7-88db-854687bd4d05">
<p local-id=3D"8333cb6ea0f1">Jonan explained that managed P3 incidents are =
raised to prevent major incidents and typically require a technical bridge,=
 while normal P3 incidents have minimal impact and do not require a bridge.=
</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"5007df7f7257" id=3D"id-20260507-Lapu-LapuGOCCandJapan-Runbo=
okandrecoveryplans">Runbook and recovery plans</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"869c63db-2f0e-4107-a7ff-04988b856242">
<li local-id=3D"90bd8795-c8d7-447b-8da7-ab09903916e6">
<p local-id=3D"a290d65ee07d">Jonan and George clarified that the rapid reco=
very action plan, if available, should be included in the runbook provided =
by the application team and accessible to the incident response team.</p></=
li>
<li local-id=3D"013c6b39-f1ed-4cb9-9652-bb2ac846ac15">
<p local-id=3D"87604529c273">Jonan explained that rapid recovery plans shou=
ld be included in the runbook provided by the application team and accessib=
le in ServiceNow for each business application.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"6b2efe0f-bf46-4905-96ee-601f14fbfe27">
<p local-id=3D"ecea30fd1666">Jonan clarified that if the automated upload o=
f rapid recovery plans to ServiceNow does not work, the team will manually =
upload the plans to ensure they are available in the CI record.</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"a281bc811c32" id=3D"id-20260507-Lapu-LapuGOCCandJapan-AIand=
automation">AI and automation</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"2add756d-89b4-48ce-92da-4d3ff47a0275">
<li local-id=3D"5af28c43-1176-456d-936f-c81dc34c7083">
<p local-id=3D"99278943c1fe">Birger shared that a pilot for chat-based ITSM=
 is currently in testing, but AI investigation is not yet used in the incid=
ent management process.</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"1aea57d44372" id=3D"id-20260507-Lapu-LapuGOCCandJapan-Incid=
entandproblemcorrelation">Incident and problem correlation</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"28c35483-5e9a-4f08-aecc-d51159870b02">
<li local-id=3D"0cafc2e2-d6d8-4d3e-8839-827f2f281944">
<p local-id=3D"2f970b2d6fe9">George stated that when an incident is related=
 to an existing problem, the incident management team links the incident ti=
cket to the open problem ticket in ServiceNow.</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"917eb5414f55" id=3D"id-20260507-Lapu-LapuGOCCandJapan-Incid=
entresponseworkflow">Incident response workflow</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"f4da1f06-67b0-4211-8907-f46d450e9877">
<li local-id=3D"ac140509-ef13-40ce-ba15-db712f199f30">
<p local-id=3D"1eef0d1a25b2">Jonan described that the ServiceNow support gr=
oup label should match the XMatters group to ensure seamless engagement dur=
ing incident response, and discrepancies are corrected during onboarding.</=
p></li>
<li local-id=3D"eb251cc0-2d9c-4442-8a6c-7b5b08a03ac4">
<p local-id=3D"f7cb421411fb">George confirmed that contact information for =
support groups is updated in both ServiceNow and XMatters during applicatio=
n onboarding to ensure accurate routing.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"fa7a49fa-4650-48d9-82b9-49e9333eaa5e">
<p local-id=3D"c0d598bc802e">Birger mentioned that Yegor and Tada are worki=
ng on cleaning up XMatters group rosters, and previously Dennis provided a =
roster dump for Japan.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"2185c0b6-47ac-4c90-b984-778713ff4d1c">
<p local-id=3D"4e2a4f82e3e0">Birger highlighted the need to set up escalati=
on flows (L1, L2, L3) in XMatters for proper incident escalation, as curren=
t Japan groups lack escalation beyond initial contacts.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"ae1b9589-b059-4a6c-9b1f-c2174c62b98c">
<p local-id=3D"d4a23f399d1f">Jonan explained that most Japan groups in XMat=
ters currently lack escalation beyond the initial contact, resulting in sta=
tic, single-level rosters.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"73808139-3233-41cf-94b7-4e4cd460c020">
<p local-id=3D"0410da8f568f">Birger and Jonan discussed that escalation flo=
ws (L1, L2, L3) can be configured in XMatters by adding groups as escalatio=
n members, allowing for multi-level incident escalation.</p></li>
</ul>
<h1 local-id=3D"b22d90f8b3b5" id=3D"id-20260507-Lapu-LapuGOCCandJapan-Follo=
w-uptasks">Follow-up tasks</h1>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"5631af6b-1cef-4172-9711-6ca=
939653bdd" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr data-local-id=3D"3544269c-722f-4898-83c1-fe21e459681a">
<td data-local-id=3D"77e458c5-726f-4d31-8a89-351311f1fff0" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"55794e68d35e">Task</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"1cc4d519-f87b-4eab-8adf-df2a9ed6b8bb" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"7b95d200998b">Assigned to</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"37f38b16-c142-4018-8b01-5d8b2c6d6aaa" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"c09c76e59988">Due date</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"dae42855-44cf-462c-8e10-8c8e59c7d149" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"da8f9e38071b">Bucket</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"2d59cbb2-902a-4c35-b7f9-2b549a2e02a3">
<td data-local-id=3D"0eb8d440-acea-4610-aec7-bb3fcdf26f5a" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"a33728f7e19e">Generate XMatters roster report for all Japan =
groups and share with David (Jonan)</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"a84aa41b-d29e-42b6-8d06-829eee4cd684" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"642905a63664">Jonan</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"59636f96-07c7-4a6a-81d5-f4f1e53da98e" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"f0341aad5440"></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"6e928d62-7873-4a67-881d-dbca20394279" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"36173657f360"></p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"66cda1fa-94c5-4737-8880-8d63744026c9">
<td data-local-id=3D"54ef0ffe-3567-41e4-9d3f-525720c83863" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"4e5eaa2b9f6b">Define the L1, L2, L3 escalation structure for=
 Ingenium onboarding and identify necessary support groups (Birger, Jonan)<=
/p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"0325ca08-06f9-4ec5-83e0-0f6ee6a382d1" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"744bcda94c70"></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"11cbc2c2-7861-40f5-b7de-7576fae7857d" class=3D"conflue=
